<Layout title="ETA Business Acquirer Mortgages · Florida Search Fund &amp; Self-Funded Acquirers &mdash; SBA 7(a) + Acquired-CEO Multi-Source Qualifying" description="Florida ETA Entrepreneurship Through Acquisition acquirer mortgage sub-page covering five practice categories: traditional search fund searcher operating with investor-funded search budget typical $80K-$150K stipend plus search expenses for 18-30 month search runway in exchange for first right to invest in acquisition plus step-up equity participation Stanford GSB Search Fund Primer plus Harvard Business School ETA standard frameworks targeting $3M-$50M revenue business acquisitions; self-funded searcher pursuing ETA without traditional search fund structure using personal capital plus bank financing plus sometimes SBA 7(a) lending more flexible timing plus deal sizing typically $1M-$10M revenue acquisitions lower equity dilution at acquisition since no search fund investor stake greater personal financial risk concentration; CEO of acquired company post-acquisition operating company with negotiated W-2 $200K-$400K typical sometimes higher for larger acquisitions plus dividends or distributions from acquired entity $250K-$1M+ plus earn-out provisions tied to performance milestones 1-3 years post-acquisition plus step-up equity vesting over multi-year period 25-30% common over 5-7 years for traditional search fund structure; independent sponsor or acquisition entrepreneur pursuing multi-deal acquisition strategy without committed fund finding deals plus raising capital deal-by-deal plus taking carry without management fee economics deal sourcing fee typical 1-2% of enterprise value at closing plus ongoing management fee modest if any plus carry or promote on exit typical 15-25% of profits above hurdle more episodic plus back-loaded vs traditional search fund structure; search fund investor or LP participating in search fund ecosystem as LP investor in pre-acquisition search funding plus post-acquisition equity many former searchers transition to investor side after first acquisition exit. SBA 7(a) acquisition financing critical mechanic with personal guaranty requirement for greater than 20% equity holders typical $5M-$10M loan size for self-funded acquisitions up to $5M SBA-guaranteed portion 10-25 year amortization prevailing prime plus spread rate structure. Florida ecosystem strong with HBS plus Stanford GSB plus IESE plus INSEAD MBA programs producing substantial Florida-bound searcher pipeline plus Sun Belt corporate succession opportunity from baby boomer business owner retirements plus main street business demographic transition plus Florida small business density rank top 3 nationally plus Florida community bank SBA 7(a) lending availability including Live Oak Bank NC-based but substantial FL presence plus Newtek FL-based plus regional Florida community banks. Mortgage qualifying lifecycle stages: searcher phase using Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01 for stipend plus Asset-Depletion Non-QM strategies for searchers with substantial liquid wealth; acquisition transition phase with SBA 7(a) personal guaranty factored into DTI as contingent liability; CEO operator phase using B3-3.1-01 for W-2 plus variable income plus B3-3.4-02 partnership and S-corp for dividends or distributions from acquired entity with 2-year operating returns plus Form 1084 cash-flow analysis at acquired entity level adding back depreciation plus goodwill amortization plus business use plus entity non-cash expenses; mature operator phase with established multi-source track record plus reduced acquisition-related contingent liabilities; exit phase with substantial liquid wealth from step-up equity capital gains supporting Asset-Depletion Non-QM path. Earn-out provisions tied to performance milestones treated as variable income under B3-3.1-01 with 2-year history once earn-out begins paying. Step-up equity vesting documented for forward-looking practice picture but excluded from current qualifying until realized at exit. SBA 7(a) personal guaranty contingent liability: acquired entity debt service coverage typically 1.25-1.50x DSCR removes personal guaranty from personal DTI. Independent sponsor multi-deal acquisition entrepreneur income: deal sourcing fees plus interim management fees plus carry or promote on exit. Multi-source synthesis. Conventional Jumbo for HNW acquired-CEOs. Bank Statement Non-QM. P&L Statement Non-QM. Asset-Depletion Non-QM for searcher plus exit phases. DSCR Non-QM. Cash-Out Refinance for acquisition equity contribution. Construction-to-Perm." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/business-advisors/business-acquirer/">
